caption: Incredible food and incredible atmosphere.
This is our favorite place for lunch before attending a show at Shea's.  They have great variety on the menu and typically have some interesting daily specials.  And the desserts are excellent!
Great food and service at decent prices directly across from Shea's.
Always good food and service ...
Bartender Tom is the best

Thanks to Lisa and the staff at Bijou for getting my mother and me a table so last minute. We were stuck in traffic before our show at Shea’s and Lisa went and spoke with the kitchen and they got us our drinks and dinner in record time, and it was all delicious!
Great Sea scallops tonight for Curtain Up. Todd the bartender did a great job
Delicious
Authentic, tasty, and fin
Great Location Service and Food & Company Fun Wow
We had a good time here and enjoyed the food.
Nice location nice atmosphere but unfortunately are unorganized and don’t properly process staff nor pay them accordingly. Don’t advise anyone to apply there.

american food and the feeling at this spot is very good. I love eating here. Looking forward to coming back with my relatives. It has an awesome atmosphere. Menu is similar to a restaurant in Jacksonville I liked.
Elegant food at reasonable price.
Service was extremely friendly.  The food was good and just the right portion size.  We went before a show at Shea's and didn't want leftovers.  I would definitely return.
Great place for before or after a show at sheas. Great food made from fresh ingredients. Reasonably priced
Terrific place for dinner pre-theater.

Burger was really good. Waiter Craig was great. I would avoid the crab and artichoke dip. It was not very good. Crab is a sweet tasting meat and this was not. I'd guess from a can but just a guess. All things considered..... pretty good.
The Bijou has become iconic and it's over 30 years of existence. Michael's stuffed peppers always satisfy. They have plenty of salads as meals. Listen carefully as their specials are always good.
Great food awesome staff, right across from Shea's
They were accommodating,  food was delicious! Enjoyed the service!
Nice little place, food was good, met the owner and she was very nice and sweet.
Great food better service by our waitress Kristen
Helped get in and out quickly before the show.
Wonderful food. Took a bit of time but it was a very busy night! Our waiter jeremy was very attentive and polite. Our experience was great!
My favorite restaurant in the theatre district.
Went before a show at Shea’s. Food came out in around 15 minutes. Definitely microwaved. Out dated and over priced. Way better places to eat in buffalo

Had the most amazing dinner. As a parent of 2 boys ages 4 and 6 dinner can be challenging especially at a restaurant. It was also a tske mom on a date night and catch a show at sheas across the street. We didnt make a reservation but were able to seat quickly. The dinner selections were amazing.   The crab cakes were perfect. Nice snd hot and well cooked. The salad and dressing was also delicious with the crab cakes. I had the lobster ravioli and it was delicious. The kids crushed their meals (flat bread pizza and home made penne with meatballs) also the fresh table bread and finished it off with their brownie sunday. Kids literally licked their plates clean which rarely happens its usually a fight to eat all their food. Service was amazing and drinks were perfect. Even just a dounle whiskey and cola was done to perfection. The perfect amount of each slight taste of whiskey slight taste of cola. Rarely do i leave a restaurant having the perfect experience but had one this night. Thanks bijou! We are never disappointed when dinning with you but this night was just perfection on everything! The only thing i would say as a con is the beer selection. Would have liked to see more local stuff from resurgence woodcock and the likes but not enough to ever stop me from coming back.

(Translated by Google) The salad was fresh and the amount was very good. It was good that you could take out and choose the contents according to your taste. The staff were very friendly and the atmosphere of the store was good.  (Original) サラダが新鮮で量もありとても美味しかった。テイクアウト可能で好みに応じて中身を選べるのも良かった。スタッフの対応も良く店の雰囲気も良かった。
Food was awesome and staff was so friendly.
Great food and services
Regular, come here weekly for lunch. Must try the Stuffed Mushrooms and the Banana Peoper Chicken Sandwich. Great people.

The place was completely empty at lunch on a weekday downtown. Food took almost 30 minutes to come out, ridiculous. Even more ridiculous was that the waitress didn't have the keys to the register and took ten minutes to get change for one of our party while they were tracked down. Food was ok, and waitress was good with refills, but overall i would never try doing lunch here again.
Excellent service, great food
Great spot down town.
Our waitress was absolutely the best. She was funny, kind and professional. The food was very good & well prepared. The atmosphere was very relaxed.
The food was good
The waitress was the best, she help me to find the best way to get to the falls. The beer and the soup were amazing!! The soup was 1 dollar more expensive than what is published in internet

Had great experience.  Recently, my Husband and Daughter had vip tickets at Town Ballroom event. I went to Bijou to hang at bar for an hr before general admission at concert.  I felt so comfortable sitting at bar alone with the nice bartende. The reg nice hostess chatted with me awhile about Sheas.  My meal was great n i even surprised the bartender when i ordered dessert.  Ahh, live it up n enjoy the experience of living. Had the crab brie n articoke dip n apple crisp w ice cream. Yum
Went for drinks, nice people.
Right across the street from Sheas Theater. Food is great prices are good.

I will NEVER go back here again. I had a reservation for 5 and I'm still waiting for SALADS at 6:17. When I walked in, there we're no other tables, and it got busy after I got here. When we tried ask out waitress for an ETA or if there was any food we could get out quickly, she snapped and was snarky. Service is TERRIBLE, especially for the high prices. Go ANYWHERE else. This place is NOT worth it.
Great food! Right across the street from Shea's Theatre.
Don't serve the crowd well. Hot food served cold.

We made early reservations for dinner expecting poor service and dinner delays before the musical...but we were served very efficiently and our waiter was very attentive. We had a great time...thank you!
Delicious, friendly and prompt service.

My boyfriend is from Buffalo and swears this place used to be good, but the eggplant was barely cooked and tasted pretty awful. He got the lobster ravioli and it was cold and the pasta was crunchy. The drinks were much better but the food was WAY overpriced and pretty damn terrible.
Great beef on weck and hamburger.  Server was excellent!
The bartender was great. The owner is miserable and angry. Foods average but you feel like an inconvenience.

Worst dining experience. Went there yesterday before Shea's and had to ask for someone to finally take our order after waiting 25 minutes. They were out of the wine we ordered then we waited forever for our meals. Asked for bread while waiting and they ran out of that too! When our food finally arrived we had about 5 minutes to eat it before we had to leave. The food was bland too, can't believe we paid for that garbage! They must stay in business just because of Shea's! Safe to say we will never be back either!
Great food at fair prices. Excellent service
We stopped without a reservation and they made a place for us to sit even though they were VERY VERY busy . Will definatly visit again next time I come to Shea's

Ate there after Shea's performance around 4:45  so it would be exceptionally busy between 5-5:30. Not sure why as our food was just ok for the price.. Was greated by a very nice women at the door and our waitress Brandy was very nice! I didn't like seeing the older women (maybe the owner) standing by the cooks area hovering while staring at all of us in that tiny room Let me say she didn't ever look happy and she never greeted anyone with a smile on her face.. I felt very uncomfortable. I had pecan chicken crusted chicken salad, the chicken was good but there was just a med amount of the spring mix lettuce 4oz of chicken and gorgonzola cheese that's it.. I thought kind of small for the price and it really was just good not really good. I won't be back and big part of the reason is the woman/owner/managers presence at all times

Went here for dinner before going to Sheas, and it's safe to say I will never come back. Our waitress was very nice, but we were forgotten about on several occasions. Our food took forever to get to our table, and it was extremely bland. We ordered meatballs, and they were extremely mushy and did not taste good. After our waitress finally brought us our food, she came by to check on us once, and then we didn't see her again for another half hour. While sitting around waiting for service, we noticed other people looking around for a waitress, and trying to get their attention. When our waitress finally appeared again, we ordered the chocolate LAVA cake. Supposed to be warm, right? The cake was cold, as was the "lava" inside the cake. Then when it came time for the bill, we had to get up and physically go ask for it because it was taking so long, and we were running out of time. I will never come back, nor recommend it to anyone.

Arrived at this restaurant around 6:15 on Oct 28. We were seeing a play right across the street at 8 pm and thought we had ample time. Told our server Robert we are seeing a play at 8. This was the WORST service my party of 4 ever rec’d. He was forgetful, didn’t bring what we asked for. We ordered our food with our drinks as we wanted to enjoy our meal. It took over and hour food to arrive (restaurant wasn’t at capacity). When our food came I requested our bill as I knew service was terrible, I had to ask twice and even though we asked for separate bills he brought one check. By this time we had 10 minutes to show time, I just quickly paid still tipped him and left. Next day reviewing the bill I see he charged us $19 for a meal we never got. My sister initially ordered the Chicken caprese gluten free, he came back 15 minutes later to say can’t guarantee its gluten free so she changed to Caponatina pasta but our incompetent Robert never removed it from the check. We were in such a rush I didn’t notice we were over charged. Poor service, decent food and over billed. I will never eat here ever again.
Great selections. Pleasant waitress. Great place for dinner before a show at Shea's across the street.

Dead quiet on a late Saturday afternoon. Attentive and friendly service was a plus. Herb oil and bread were a good start but the food itself was pretty disappointing for the price point.  With tip $35 for the two items pictured. The first a sample of their meatballs (soft with good texture, but very bland) and stuffed pepper (again bland but slightly cheesier filling) for I believe $9. The other was their chicken caprese. Two small medallions of chicken and 1-1.5 cups of orzo. Pretty meager portion and one dimensional flavor for $19.  My dinner compatriot got their spaghetti and meatballs which oddly came with two smaller meatballs (maybe 50% smaller, just as bland) and watery 'marinara'
Great food
Went for lunch, party of 9, service was amazing, food was delicious! Not just a dinner spot. New menu was rolled out the day we went, not sure what the other menu was, but this one was nice!
This is an excellent restaurant right across from Shea's theatre. People often go here for dinner before a show. I love the pesto they serve with warm bread before the meal arrives.
Good food and right across from Shea's. Get there earlier if you're going to a show. It fills up fast!
Just had a drink there before shea's

Great location in the heart of the theater district.  If you're headed to Sheas or another theater then this is a good choice for dinner.  I recommend the five cheese haddock.  Reasonable prices, reservations recommended.
They always have great food! Never had a disappointing experience here.
Great food! Nice bar. Don't usually need a reservation unless there is a show at Sheas Theater.
Consistent service and food.
Sometimes the service is a bit slow but the food is good and in summertime it's nice to sit by the window and just people watch. They always have great specials, too.
The flatbreads are delicious! I stopped in for a quick dinner and wasn't disappointed. I had a friend with me and we enjoyed the service and atmosphere of the place.
An unexpected surprise.  Awesome crabcakes.

Currently, I can't find a better burger downtown. Ulrich's is right up there, but Bijou staff is outstanding and friendly, and after ordering the same thing 2 or 3 times, they remember exactly what the customer wants and how they like their food prepared.  While I'm a big fan of their burger, I've had other entrees, too, and have never had anything to complain about. I highly recommend the Bijou.
Really never had a bad meal the atmosphere and  people  just fine
Always a great place to eat. Very close to Sheas. Staff is very friendly and helpful. Food is always of good quality. We eat there whenever we go to Sheas.
